Mentha piperita

   [2099.gif]
   Authority L.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Asteridae:Lamiales:Labiatae
   Synonyms Mentha x piperita, Mentha aquatica x spicata
   Common names peppermint, brandy mint, menthe poivree, menthe, bohe,
   Pfefferminze, menta, pepparmynta, pepermynte, na'na, pepermunt,
   hortela, myata, seiyo-hakka, Folia Menthae piperitae, Oleum Menthae
   piperitae, Spiritus Menthae piperitae, Menthae piperitae herba,
   Aetheroleum menthae piperitae, yang-po-ho
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 2099

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A strongly scented, often branched herb reaching a
   height of 0.3-1 m. The leaves are oblong ovate, dark green with violet
   veins. USES An essential oil is extracted from the leaves. The oil
   contains about 50% menthol and is used in food, flavor, and
   pharmaceutical products. Dried leaves are used in herbal teas, fruit
   jams, and desserts. The oil is thought to be a natural carminative with
   some antispasmodic properties. KILLING T The underground stolons can
   survive -17 or even -30°C in the case of snow cover. Young shoots may
   tolerate -8°C. GROWING PERIOD Perennial. First shoots may be harvested
   40-55 days from planting of divided rootstocks. For tea production 2-3
   cuttings can be taken per year and for harvest of essential oil usually
   1 harvest per year is taken. Plantations should be maintained for 2,
   or, rarely 3 years. The crop should not be cultivated in the same field
   for 4 years. COMMON NAMES Peppermint, Menthe poivree, Pfefferminze,
   Menta peperina. FURTHER INF Altitudes in the tropics above 1000 m are
   generally suitable for peppermint. Average annual yield is 12-20 t/ha
   of green plant, and 30-65 kg/ha of essential oil. The harvest is
   usually divided on a first cutting which may be 7-14 t/ha and a second
   cutting of 5-8 t/ha of green plant.

   Sources
   SOURCES (Mentha x piperita L.)
   Hackett C 1982 pp 22 [FER, PHO, DEP, PH, TEXT, TEMP]
   Tindall H 1983 pp 245 [DRA, TEXT, RAIN, TEMP]
   Duke J 1975 pp 21 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 100 [USE]
   Prakash V 1990 pp 49-52 [FER, DRA, TEXT, LIG, USE]
   Hornok L 1992 pp 187-195 [KTMP, TEMP, LIG, PHO, DEP, RAIN, DRA, TEXT,
   FER, USE]
   Langer R 1991 pp 285-287 [TEMP, RAIN, PH, FER, USE]

